The paper discusses the use of machine learning for protein function prediction, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on testing the quality of these prediction tools, which involves evaluating the performance of the machine learning models, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges associated with conducting systematic testing, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) concern. Finally, the paper proposes the use of metamorphic testing, which is a technique used in software testing and verification (cs.CE).
